                "Cyclotron Laboratory, East Lansing"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The secondary 9Be target with thickness of (188+-",
                "4)mg/cm2 was placed at the target position of the",
                "S800 spectrograph"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Reaction residues were momentum analyzed",
                "using high resolution S800 spectrograph. Reaction",
                "residues were identified in focal plane detector."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Energy loss in the S800 ion chamber, time",
                "of flight taken between scintillators, and the",
                "position and angle information of the reaction",
                "products in the focal plane of the spectrograph were",
                "employed to unambiguously identify the reaction",
                "residues"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Fifteen 32-fold segmented HPGe detectors were",
                "arranged at a distance of 20 cm from the secondary",
                "target in two rings with central angles of 90deg and",
                "37deg relative to the beam axis."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "EDE",
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The gamma-ray spectra were detected",
                "in coincidence with the knockout reaction residues",
                "Gamma rays emitted in flight were event-by-event",
                "reconstructed for Doppler shift."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A multicomponent beam consisting of the N=16 isotones",
                "32S, 33Cl, and 34Ar was obtained by fragmentation of",
                "a 150 MeV/nucleon 36Ar primary beam. The 9Be",
                "fragmentation target with thickness of 1034 mg/cm2",
                "was located at the midacceptance target position of",
                "the A1900 fragment separator. Composition of the final",
                "incoming beam was",
                "Projectile       Everage energy  Beam composition",
                "                      (MeV/A)          (%)",
                "   32S                  62.8            8",
                "   33Cl                 66.4           16",
                "   34Ar                 70.0           76"
              ]
            }
          ],
